hyperopia or hypermetropia , from the greek word " hyper - metropia : ὑπερ-μετρωπία " ( hyper = over + metro = measure + op = sight , look + suffix ia = condition , state > thus a condition of over - measured sight ) commonly known as   farsightedness ( american english ) or longsightedness ( british english ) , is a defect of vision caused by an imperfection in the eye ( often when the eyeball is too short or the lens can not become round enough ) , causing the eye to not have enough power to see in the distance , causing the eye to have to accommodative , by having to make the lens of the eye more convex , or plus .

the human body : hyperopia , the opposite of myopia , is commonly called this

farsightedness